>> confirm this, but my suspicion is that they are image maps.

> That's me!  <g>

> The Jogger uses Image maps.  The mythological creatures all use textures...no
> image maps.  The hair on their heads, is done by applying the WRINKLED
> texture. If the Z axis goes through the tops of the head, the settings are
> something like z=10, x=.5, y=.5.  This will create long but thin wrinkles
> that look like clumps of hair strands. The fuzz on the bodies of the
> Centaur, Minotaur, and Satyr are done with the FUZZ.ITX.

> For a lion...the wrinkled texture would work very well.  In my example above,
> the Z axis should be rotated so it's almost perpendicular to the  orientation
> of the mane:
____
|    \
y___________\_____z        Acutally, should be rotated down from the Y
|       |     \            axis a bit.  Play with it.
|        \_____|
|
x

> Please repost to IML if you like.

> -GreG tsadilas

