@node IML-68 " MSG-68  Subject: Re: Bump maps on a cylinder."

Subject: Re: Bump maps on a cylinder.
Date: Wed, 14 Sep 1994 16:56:17 -0400 (EDT)
From: jgoldman@acs.bu.edu

> 
> Charles wrote
> > Michael,
> > 
> > I don't know if it has been cured in 3.0, but yes, previous versions of 
> > Imagine would ignore the "repeat" button when the wrap mode was set to 
> > anything other than FlatX/FlatZ. 
> In the Bible, ie, "Understanding Imagine 2.0" Mr. Worsley says that 
> it's a BUG of Imagine.

	And in the 3.0 Manual, Impulse says that you *can't* repeat
brushmaps (via 'repeat' box) on anything other than flat
wraps. So in a way it's a bug (it won't do what we want it to), and in
a way (a little more accurately) it's officially not a function...

							J.---->
E-Mail: jgoldman@acs.bu.edu



