@node IML-72 " MSG-72  Subject: Looping Anim"

Subject: Looping Anim
Date: Wed, 14 Sep 94 20:56:11 EDT
From: mtucibat@cris.com (Mike Tucibat)

On 9-14, Mike McCool wrote:

M> Back to basics on this one.  I'm trying to make a simple movie of 
M> a plane that orbits a revolving earth.  I'd like the thing to loop, 
M> endlessly. 
M> 
M> I keep getting a little skip, or stutter, when the loop starts 
M> over.  And when I let Imagine do it's looping anim thing, appending two 
M> frames, it looks even worse.  The plane and the earth jump backwards.
======================

        Just a quick thought...
        
        If you have the start and end frames identical, you should
        only use eg. 29 of 30 frames for the anim.  And in that case,
        you wouldn't want to make a repeating anim.

        -mikeT



