@node IML-75 " MSG-75  Subject: ReBoot"

Subject: ReBoot
Date: Wed, 14 Sep 1994 21:39:26 -0600
From: beeton@SEDSystems.ca (Gary Beeton, beeton@SEDSystems.ca)

Greetings,

I just finished watching a TV show called ReBoot.  It is a half-hour kids show 
produced *ENTIRELY* using 3-D CG animation.  The premise of the show is almost
identical to TRON, except there is no rotoscoping involved here.  They seem to 
go out of their way to make it look CG, but they achieve some pretty good 
organic effects too (including humanoid characters with credible facial
expressions).  I didn't manage to catch enough of the credits to determine the 
computer platform or software they used, but I did note that it is produced in 
Vancouver, Canada.  It plays Wednesday evenings on YTV (Canada). For those who 
can, I highly recommend a watch.  Very Cool!!

Gary
beeton@SEDSystems.ca



