@node IML-79 " MSG-79  Subject: Re: Black lines on reflective objects."

Subject: Re: Black lines on reflective objects.
Date: Thu, 15 Sep 1994 18:15:40 -0500 (EST)
From: leyen@inf.ufrgs.br (Christian Leyen)

Hi, I had the same problem some time ago.
This happens when you use a picture that doesn't "fill" all the columns
of its resolution. In some paint programs it is impossible (or difficult)
to access all the columns in an overscan image, so when you save the
picture, these columns are all black. When Imagine uses this picture as
a global brush, these black columns appear in the reflections.
One solution is to load the picture in an image proccessing program (ADpro,
ImageFX) and crop it to remove the black columns, and then save it again.

Christian Leyen (leyen@inf.ufrgs.br)
~""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""~


