@node IML-96 " MSG-96  Subject: Imagine for Macs"

Subject: Imagine for Macs
Date: Mon, 19 Sep 94 18:36:00 -0100
From: torgeir.holm@tbc.bbs.no (Torgeir Holm)

>On a side-note, does the Amiga Imagine have its work area
>displayed in some sort of window on the Imagine screen?
>A gadgetless window at that.  I'm wondering because it is
>possible to lose system requesters behind the Imagine
>work area if you hit the requester's depth gadget.  If the
>requester is near the title bar there is a 1pixel gap in
>which you may be able to pull the requester back up front.
>I don't lose them often, its only happened accidentally.
>But it is annoying and has made me wonder if the work area
>is a custom window rather than a screen that I thought it
>was.

You're absolutely right. The work area is a window. If you lose a
requester behind this window, you will lock up the program until you
get the requester back :(

If you use the commodity Yak, you will be able to send the work area to
the back with a LMB->RMB mouseclick. This will get you your requesters
back.

BTW: Try resizing the work area with DragIt4, works just like any other
window. ecept that the contents are cropped, not scaled.


Torge!r


