Well, even so, I've found that if you fiddle with the RGB values of your
world's lighting, you can really improve the darkness of the pictures in the
manual.  For example, I set my desk lamp's values to 255,255,255 (blindingly
bright).  If I then stare at the lamp for a while, everything begins to go
black.  Then when I look at the pictures in the manual, they don't seem nearly
as dark anymore.  Of course, it takes a few hours for my eyesight to return to
normal, but who ever said reading manuals was *easy* ?!?!?

