@node IML-131 " MSG-131  Subject: Quasi-marble texture"

Subject: Quasi-marble texture
Date: Thu, 22 Sep 1994 10:48:30 -0400 (EDT)
From: Rob Freundlich <RSF@mother.idx.com>

I was trying to make a marble texture last night in Imagine 2.0 (no Essence)
and stumbled into something interesting.  I made my object a pale white
(190-ish on all the RGB sliders), high Shiny value, high Hardness, low
Roughness, Specular just a few shades below the object color, ummm, possibly
others as well.

I then applied two wood textures.  The textures are rotated with respect to
each other.  Both have very wide bands (and a low number of bands) and a large
Variation value (for "burl" effect, according to Understanding Imagine).  The
color of each texture is a darker shade of grey than the object, and the two
textures have slightly different colors.

My object is a dome-shape, and the result looks quite a bit like marble.  Doing
the same with a black object and very dark shades gave a dark marble-ish look,
although I'm not entirely happy with it yet.

When I get them finished, I'll post the images and objects to the net.

---
