@endnode 
 
@node IML-187 " MSG-187  Subject: QR versus ProjectRender, thanks"

Subject: QR versus ProjectRender, thanks
Date: Sat, 24 Sep 1994 13:59:00 -0400
From: david.wyand@canrem.com (David Wyand)

Hi Mike!

> I do my quickrender, Ham laced, in stage, and it displays
>automatically.  My object has a nice grainy texture.  I render the very
>scene in the Project editor, 24bit ILBM, Ham.  I click on Show. I'm
shown
>the same scene, but my object has lost its nice grainy texture and has
>that wave phenomenon all over the surfaces. I've even tried making both
>QR and ProjectRender ILBM or RGBN, it doesn't matter: the difference
>between the two images is still pronounced.

I think I've noticed your problem by your above description.  If you are
using Laced HAM as your quickrender, why not do the same for the
Project?  When creating the project, choose from one of the defaults;
namely, the Laced HAM one.  This will set the mode to 12bit ILBM (which
is HAM) and the Laced button should be clicked.

What is happening is that your are choosing the 24-bit option bu
probably don't have the Auto Dither button depressed.  This causes the
picture to be displayed in HAM mode but with no dithering, hence the
'wave phenomenon' you describe.  I think that the best way around all
this is to just render in 12-bit ILBM as described above.

Of course, if you had ADPro, you could take the 24-bit image and convert
it to HAM, but no guarentees as to the likeness to the quickrender
picture.  This is how I do it, though, for the final render at least.

                                        -Dave
                                         david.wyand@canrem.com

Questions?  Just ask...


